race.comment: Tough EYES WIDE SHUT (5) is in a top metro stable and looked a run short at Mornington first up. Has been freshened and kept up to the mark with placed jumpouts at Flemington and Mornington. Has a close-up placing this track and trip in the back-form and he can use the inside barrier. QUBELLA (8) seeks the hat-trick off wins at the picnics. She tas TAB form good enough and will be fitter again. Rates well and don't underestimate. KENTAHTEN (1) doesn't win out of turn but he improved beaten a whisker two back and raced favourite at Wangaratta following, and it was an even effort. Has a 2kg claim and can get into the finish in this lineup. ALMIGHTY WILL (4) is third-up with more to offer. He's been giving away starts, and the extra metres will suit. Has pieces of form that would see him in the finish. SPIRIT ANGEL (9) resumed in good order but is another who finds it hard to win.
